You can get help from professional organisations that can put you in touch with a qualified rating surveyor. 

They will normally belong to one of the following organisations:

- [Royal Institution of Chartered Surveyors (RICS)](http://www.rics.org/ "Royal Institution of Chartered Surveyors"){:rel="external"}
- [Institute of Revenues, Rating and Valuation (IRRV)](http://www.irrv.net/HOME/ "Institute of Revenues, Rating and Valuation"){:rel="external"}
- [Rating Surveyors Association](http://www.ratingsurveyorsassociation.org/ "Rating Surveyors Association"){:rel="external"}

You may be charged for any advice you get from these bodies right from the start. 

You can call the RICS enquiry line on 0870 333 1600 for advice from a local chartered surveyor. The first 30 minutes are free. 

*[VOA]: Valuation Office Agency
*[RICS]: Royal Institution of Chartered Surveyors
